?quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/velosamba-cream-310e9b3.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1111%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/velosamba-cream-310e9b3.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1667%2C1111 3x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img class=\"wp-image-620978 align size-landscape_thumbnail image-handler__image image-handler__image--aspect no-wrap js-lazyload\" data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/velosamba-cream-310e9b3.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Adidas Velosamba\" title=\"Adidas Velosamba\"></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></picture></div><div class=\"caption-hold\"><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\"><span class=\"caption-copy\"><i class=\"icon-arrow icon-camera-circle\"></i> The shoe is available in four different colours.</span></figcaption><span class=\"im-image-caption\"> <i>Adidas</i></span></div>\n<p>The Velosamba is available in four different colours: black, cream, acid yellow (our pick of the bunch) and navy.</p>\n<p>The Velosamba is available exclusively from Adidas for £100 / $120 / €120.</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://knl.mntzrlt.net/shop-rest/api/link/wrapper/608/12?mk=GBP_EN&amp;su=https%3A%2F%2Fpublishers.monetizer101.com%2Fhub%2Frelinker%2Findex.html&amp;tu=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adidas.co.uk%2Fthe-velosamba-cycling-shoes%2FFY4485.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Buy the Velosamba direct from Adidas</a></li>\n</ul><section class=\"highlight \"><div class=\"highlight__content editor-content\">\n        <h2>A hint of more to come from Adidas?</h2>\n<p>At the time of the launch of The Road Shoe, Adidas was clear it was taking its re-entry into the cycling market seriously, and hinted that we should expect more from the brand going forward. </p>\n<p>The brand also stressed that the shoe was targeted at the “young and burgeoning generation of [new] cyclists”. </p>\n<p>With that in mind, the launch of the Velosamba should come as no surprise – cycling has experienced a boom in popularity over the past year and enormous brands such as Adidas will be keen to cash in on the growth. </p>\n<p>Whether Adidas will move into the ‘serious’ enthusiast sphere or make a re-entry into the professional peloton seems unlikely at this stage – the focus appears to be on the entry-level and commuter market, but we will certainly be watching the brand closely. </p>\n<p>\n\n    </p></div>\n    </section>","author":"Jack Luke","siteTitle":"BikeRadar","siteHash":"df99dd1320fcd97327a2def4c67247c08cd4090a7dab684a0eddb9b856f80ef1","entryHash":"54be419d0382eb00209bb5d7e0e841a966197b38dc913819b87c4fff8fd4356d","category":"Cycling"}